# {{PASCAL_NAME}}

Next.js web app using the BFF (Backend-for-Frontend) pattern.

## Architecture

- **Next.js 15** with App Router, Server/Client Components
- **BFF pattern**: Next.js is a thin frontend layer — all business logic lives in the NestJS backend
- **Data fetching**: Server Components use `apiFetch<T>()`, Client Components use TanStack Query
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first config), shadcn/ui components
- **Auth**: Better Auth (not next-auth), session managed via NestJS backend
- **Testing**: Vitest + @testing-library/react + jsdom

## Key Rules

- Server Components fetch from backend — no direct DB access
- Client Components use TanStack Query for caching/polling
- No API routes except: auth catch-all, markdown proxy, llms.txt
- Use `buildSiteMetadata()` from `@/lib/seo/metadata` — never hardcode metadata
- Use Biome for linting (not ESLint)

## SEO & AI Readability Infrastructure

This app includes built-in SEO and AI optimization. **Keep it updated on every change.**

### What to Update When Adding/Changing Routes

| Change | Files to Update |
|--------|----------------|
| New public page/route | `src/app/sitemap.ts` — add URL entry |
| New public page/route | `src/app/llms.txt/route.ts` — add page to manifest |
| New content type (article, product, etc.) | `src/lib/seo/json-ld.ts` — add schema builder |
| New page with unique content | Add `generateMetadata()` export to the page file |
| New page with structured data | Add `<JsonLdScript>` with appropriate schema |
| New admin/private section | `src/app/robots.ts` — add to disallow list |
| New API route | `src/app/robots.ts` — already disallows `/api/` |

### SEO File Reference

| File | Purpose | When to Touch |
|------|---------|---------------|
| `src/app/sitemap.ts` | Dynamic sitemap.xml generation | Every new public route |
| `src/app/robots.ts` | Crawl rules (standard + AI bots) | New private sections |
| `src/app/llms.txt/route.ts` | LLM discovery manifest | Every new public route |
| `src/lib/seo/metadata.ts` | `buildSiteMetadata()` — site-wide defaults | Brand/title changes |
| `src/lib/seo/json-ld.ts` | Schema.org JSON-LD builders | New content types |
| `src/lib/seo/ai-bots.ts` | AI bot user-agent detection | New AI crawlers emerge |
| `src/lib/seo/markdown-transform.ts` | HTML-to-Markdown for AI bots | Rarely |
| `src/lib/seo/sanitize.ts` | HTML sanitization before markdown | Rarely |
| `src/components/seo/json-ld-script.tsx` | JSON-LD renderer component | Rarely |
| `src/middleware.ts` | AI bot detection + markdown rewrite | New bypass rules |
| `src/app/api/markdown/[...path]/route.ts` | Markdown proxy for AI bots | Rarely |

### Checklist for New Pages

- [ ] Page has `generateMetadata()` with title and description
- [ ] Page added to `sitemap.ts`
- [ ] Page added to `llms.txt/route.ts`
- [ ] JSON-LD added if page has structured content (articles, products, FAQs, etc.)
- [ ] Private pages excluded in `robots.ts`

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | Backend API base URL |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` | Canonical site URL (used by SEO infra) |
| `PORT` | Dev server port |

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev          # Start dev server (Turbopack)
npm run build        # Production build
npm test             # Run tests
npm run type-check   # TypeScript check
npm run lint         # Biome lint
```
